2015-05-19 14:08:49	jokajak	WTF is this stow?
2015-05-19 14:08:57	Zathrus	acidrainfall: see, if you were RHEL then we could show you how Satellite saves money through Studies (TM). But, no, dead to us!
2015-05-19 14:08:58	ChibaPet	Seriously? It's been around for like 20 years.
2015-05-19 14:09:13	ChibaPet	Stow is a tool that manages symlink farms for you, to ease deployment of unpackaged software.
2015-05-19 14:09:21	jokajak	oh, i see
2015-05-19 14:09:26	Zathrus	ChibaPet: I haven't heard of it either
2015-05-19 14:09:37	ChibaPet	The software sits in, for instance, /usr/local/stow/whateverv1 and you 'stow whateverv1' to get the symlink farm set up.
2015-05-19 14:09:53	ChibaPet	It links into /usr/local/bin so things can link to libraries and such where they expect to find them.
2015-05-19 14:10:13	ChibaPet	Then when you need to upgrade - and this is where it's useful - it unlinks and relinks the new versions.
2015-05-19 14:11:01	ChibaPet	It's a bandaid where what you really want is proper packaging, but it's an amazingly useful, bulletproof, decades-tested bandaid that's trivially easy to install and use.
2015-05-19 14:11:22	Zathrus	so... it's the precursor to alternatives
2015-05-19 14:11:35	ChibaPet	I like it better than alternatives. Far, far simpler.
2015-05-19 14:11:41	ChibaPet	I really dislike alternatives syntax.
