2015-06-09 08:42:55	capt_mercaptan	I was a little annoyed that in F21 that I had installed the iptables.service and then installed fail2ban.service which uninstalled iptables.service and installed firewalld.service.  --- I was annoyed because I don't feel like it warned me it was going to do that, but oh, well. that's neither here nor there
2015-06-09 08:44:02	delhage	that's a packaging problem if anything, not a systemd problem
2015-06-09 08:44:26	capt_mercaptan	oh I know.
2015-06-09 08:44:35	capt_mercaptan	It has nothing to do with systemd.
2015-06-09 08:44:47	delhage	right
2015-06-09 08:45:07	capt_mercaptan	I was actually surprised, however, that yum uninstalled conflits without notification.
2015-06-09 08:45:26	rigeld2	capt_mercaptan: Not a conflict.
2015-06-09 08:45:44	rigeld2	capt_mercaptan: I'd bet firewalld obseletes iptables in the package
2015-06-09 08:45:45	capt_mercaptan	iptables package doesn't conflict with firewalld?
2015-06-09 08:46:12	rigeld2	Obseleting would explain that behavior.  Conflicting doesn't
2015-06-09 08:46:18	capt_mercaptan	ok
2015-06-09 08:46:35	capt_mercaptan	I haven't dealt much with obsoleting
2015-06-09 08:46:45	capt_mercaptan	at least, apparently, that I know ofg
2015-06-09 08:46:59	rigeld2	open/libreoffice was an obselete iirc
2015-06-09 08:47:31	capt_mercaptan	is obsoleting an RPM thing or a yum thing? (I want to start reading the docs in the right place)
2015-06-09 08:47:35	siXy	rpm
2015-06-09 08:47:37	MerlinTHP	RPM
2015-06-09 08:48:04	siXy	if in doubt, it's usually an rpm thing.
2015-06-09 08:48:10	 *	MerlinTHP nods solemnly.
2015-06-09 08:49:24	capt_mercaptan	"The Obsoletes dependencies are usually only used when a package is renamed, such as the apache package becoming the httpd package, starting in Red Hat Linux 8.0. The httpd package obsoletes the apache package."
2015-06-09 08:49:50	capt_mercaptan	so, this must be one of those "unusual" cases where it's not just a rename
2015-06-09 08:50:01	MerlinTHP	capt_mercaptan: http://pkgs.fedoraproject.org/cgit/libreoffice.git/tree/libreoffice.spec#n397
2015-06-09 08:50:11	MerlinTHP	etc etc
2015-06-09 08:50:18	MerlinTHP	That's the sort of usage you normally see
2015-06-09 08:50:38	siXy	capt_mercaptan: there's another case - when one of the packages is written by lennart it automatically obsoletes the other one.
